  <div class="section white">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="text-running">The WordsWorth Project envisions to bring together people in the community who are
        privileged to have experienced the joy of reading books simply for the pleasure of diving into a world hidden
        inside them. Our initiative channelizes their efforts to transform them into changemakers who work to assist
        those who are not fortunate to have the same experience simply due to the institutional deficiencies that plagues
        the country in the educational sector. By using our experiences of working in the social sector and our knowledge
        through our educational backgrounds, The WordsWorth Project teams works tirelessly to encourage primary grade
        students from marginalised communities studying in urban government schools to take up reading as a hobby.
        By training the youth teacher volunteers in the different methodologies of teaching and using book lists which
        are curated as per the students’ reading levels we try to bridge the gap that exists in the reading abilities of
        students which prevent them from enjoying the act of reading books.</p>
